#### Step 11: Migration consideration for existing plaintext records

The `decryptProfileAttributes` function (Step 3) already handles legacy records by checking `if (!profile.encryptedAttributes || !profile.attributesIV)` and falling back to returning `profile.attributes` as-is. No IndexedDB schema migration is needed since we are adding optional fields.

However, consider adding a one-time migration utility that re-encrypts existing plaintext records. This could be a function called on login:

```typescript
export async function migrateUnencryptedProfiles(): Promise<number> {
  const dek = getCurrentDEK();
  if (!dek) return 0;

  const allRaw = await profileRepo.getAll();
  let migrated = 0;

  for (const p of allRaw) {
    if (!p.encryptedAttributes && Object.keys(p.attributes).length > 0) {
      const json = JSON.stringify(p.attributes);
      const { ciphertext, iv } = await encrypt(json, dek);
      await profileRepo.put({
        ...p,
        encryptedAttributes: arrayBufferToBase64(ciphertext),
        attributesIV: uint8ArrayToBase64(iv),
        attributes: {},
        updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      });
      migrated++;
    }
  }
  return migrated;
}
```

Call this from the login flow in `auth.service.ts` or from `App.svelte` after successful authentication.

